list.item:
Pregnancy: Use only if imaging is essential during pregnancy and cannot be delayed.(


   8.1
)

text.paragraph:
After intravenous administration, gadobutrol is rapidly distributed in the extracellular space. After a gadobutrol dose of 0.1 mmol/kg body weight, an average level of 0.59 mmol gadobutrol/L was measured in plasma 2 minutes after the injection and 0.3 mmol gadobutrol/L 60 minutes after the injection. Gadobutrol does not display any particular protein binding. Following GBCA administration, gadolinium is present for months or years in brain, bone, skin, and other organs

  [see Warnings and Precautions (5.5

  )].
